oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Concurrent Infection of Young Calves With Eimeria bovis and coronavirus
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Hoblet, K. H.
Shulaw, W. P.
Saif, L. J.
Weisbrode, S. E.
Lance, S. E.
Redman, D. R.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: replicates
coronavirus infection
Eimeria bovis
bull calves
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Over a period of 3 summers, 21 colostrum-fed Holstein bull calves, 1-3 days of age, were selected to form 7 replicates, each consisting of 3 calves. The project was conducted during the summer because screen-testing of calves indicated a higher likelihood during warm months of obtaining calves without evidence of coronavirus infection.
